results.occurrenceRemarks: This blowfly was seen on the leaves of a plant outdoors, however, I also saw many others on bins, plants, and dog feces that hadn't been picked up yet. This fly in particular wasn't moving, so I was able to get a good picture. These are really common around here, especially in the summer time. This one was about the 1 cm long, and it had red bumps where I can assume its' eyes are. It's abdomen was covered in a shiny, metallic green, and it's wings were transparent.  This species is native to Asia and Africa.
